settings.label: MEDICAL INFORMATION
settings.description: You are required to advise at registration of any medical conditions or medication, knowledge of which might be vital in the event of rescue; for example, asthma or diabetes.

Due to the new race format, please note the ability for Helm to race two boats will be dependent on race scheduling.

If you require camping facilities please contact Tyn-Y-Mur using code Sail25

For further information please e-mail office@scyc.co.uk

settings.html_codes:
South Caernarvonshire Yacht Club “The Club”

Your privacy is important to us. We will handle any data we collect in line with current data protection legislation. Our full Data Privacy Statement can be found on our website at www.scyc.co.uk

Future contact
The Club would like to contact you by email in the future to give details of sailing events that may be of interest to you. Please confirm that you give consent to be contacted for this purpose.

Photographs

The Club may arrange for photographs to be taken during the sailing event and published on our website and other media channels to promote the Club. Please confirm that you give consent to your image and, if you are the parent or guardian of any child under 18 included in this entry, their image being used in this way.

settings.label: DECLARATION
settings.description:
To be signed by helm if aged over 18 

I confirm that the information given in this entry form is correct. 

  • I agree to the Abersoch Dinghy Week "Notice of Race" Conditions of Entry and have read the SCYC Health and Safety Policies and Procedures (Summary) below.

 

Link to the SCYC Health and Safety Policies and Procedures PDF https://scyc.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/SCYC-H-S-Summary.pdf

settings.label: DECLARATION - UNDER 18
settings.description:
To be signed by parent / guardian if helm under 18 

The helm is my dependant and I confirm that he / she and his / her crew are competent to take part in the Event. I confirm that I am responsible for my dependant and his / her crew throughout the Event.

  • I confirm that the information given in this entry form is correct.
  • I agree to the Abersoch Dinghy Week "Notice of Race" Conditions of Entry and have read the SCYC Health and Safety Policies and Procedures (Summary) below.
  • I confirm that, during the time that my dependant (and crew) is / are afloat, I and / or one or more of the named emergency contacts will personally be in Abersoch.

Enquiries to office@scyc.co.uk

 

 

The Abersoch Dinghy Week Team
